                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 19.647,
                                "byte_start": 100559,
                                "byte_stop": 179240,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in 75-1771, Commissioner of Internal Revenue Against Standard Life and Accident Company, and 76-423, Puyallup Tribe against Washington will be announced by Mr. Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 19.647,
                        "stop": 205.508,
                        "byte_start": 179240,
                        "byte_stop": 922580,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 19.647,
                                "stop": 30.232,
                                "byte_start": 179240,
                                "byte_stop": 221558,
                                "text": "In the tax case, we decide how a life insurance company should account for unpaid premiums in computing its federal income taxes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.232,
                                "stop": 38.066,
                                "byte_start": 221558,
                                "byte_stop": 252905,
                                "text": "An unpaid premium is an installment which is payable within the policy year, but has not been paid at the end of the calendar year."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.066,
                                "stop": 52.03,
                                "byte_start": 252905,
                                "byte_stop": 308703,
                                "text": "Thus, for example, if a policy is written on May 1, 1976, an installment due on February 1, 1977 would be an unpaid premium on December 31, 1976."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.03,
                                "stop": 60.694,
                                "byte_start": 308703,
                                "byte_stop": 343393,
                                "text": "If such a premium is not paid in due course, the policy will lapse but the company has no legal right to collect its unpaid premiums."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.694,
                                "stop": 67.942,
                                "byte_start": 343393,
                                "byte_stop": 372337,
                                "text": "For that reason, they are not typical accounts receivable and would not be accrued under normal accounting principles."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.942,
                                "stop": 79.385,
                                "byte_start": 372337,
                                "byte_stop": 418103,
                                "text": "The life insurance industry however, is subject to extensive state regulation which uniformly requires the companies to compute their reserves as though these unpaid premiums had in fact been paid."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.385,
                                "stop": 85.834,
                                "byte_start": 418103,
                                "byte_stop": 443912,
                                "text": "In general, the addition to the reserves is equal to the net valuation portion of the unpaid premium."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.834,
                                "stop": 95.015,
                                "byte_start": 443912,
                                "byte_stop": 480693,
                                "text": "That is to say the portion of the premium that state law requires to be set aside in order to enable the company to meet its policy obligation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.015,
                                "stop": 105.387,
                                "byte_start": 480693,
                                "byte_stop": 522175,
                                "text": "The so-called loading portion of the premium, which is the part of the premium that covers company expenses and profit if any, is not added to its reserves."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.387,
                                "stop": 113.272,
                                "byte_start": 522175,
                                "byte_stop": 553731,
                                "text": "It is the Government\u0027s primary position that the loading portion of unpaid premiums should also be treated as through it had been paid."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.272,
                                "stop": 118.378,
                                "byte_start": 553731,
                                "byte_stop": 574107,
                                "text": "Such treatment would increase the income tax liability of the companies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.378,
                                "stop": 134.32,
                                "byte_start": 574107,
                                "byte_stop": 637846,
                                "text": "On the other hand, the company in this case takes the position that the net valuation portion of the unpaid premium should be treated as though paid for the purpose of calculating its reserves, but should be ignored when it is calculating its assets and gross premium income."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.32,
                                "stop": 142.028,
                                "byte_start": 637846,
                                "byte_stop": 668775,
                                "text": "That approach, which was accepted by the Court of Appeals in this case, tends to decrease the company\u0027s tax liability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.028,
                                "stop": 158.042,
                                "byte_start": 668775,
                                "byte_stop": 732827,
                                "text": "We reject both of these positions and hold that the net valuation portion of the premium should be treated as paid in calculating reserves, assets and gross premium income, and that the loading portion should be excluded from all these calculations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.042,
                                "stop": 169.385,
                                "byte_start": 732827,
                                "byte_stop": 778175,
                                "text": "This is the accounting procedure followed since 1871 by an official organization responsible for auditing insurance companies on behalf of various state regulatory agencies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.385,
                                "stop": 180.102,
                                "byte_start": 778175,
                                "byte_stop": 821016,
                                "text": "Congress has directed the companies to follow that organization\u0027s approach in various situations and we read that statutory direction as controlling in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.102,
                                "stop": 188.629,
                                "byte_start": 821016,
                                "byte_stop": 855080,
                                "text": "We accordingly reverse the contrary judgement of the Court of Appeals for the Tenth Circuit and remand for further proceedings consistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.629,
                                "stop": 199.326,
                                "byte_start": 855080,
                                "byte_stop": 897921,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice White, with whom the Chief Justice has joined, has filed a separate opinion dissenting from our analysis but agreeing that the judgment of the Court of Appeals must be set aside."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.326,
                                "stop": 205.508,
                                "byte_start": 897921,
                                "byte_stop": 922580,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stewart took no part in the consideration or decision of this case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
